# MAS-PaperHelper

Runnable project skeleton with configurable data sources.

## Quick Start

1. Install base dependencies

```bash
uv sync --extra dev
```

Optional integrations:

```bash
uv sync --extra google --extra vector --extra database
```

2. Run one-shot workflow from CLI

```bash
uv run python scripts/main.py run-once --user-id quant_researcher_01
```

3. Start scheduler loop

```bash
uv run python scripts/main.py schedule --interval-seconds 300
```

4. Start web app

```bash
uv run uvicorn web.app:app --reload
```

Open http://127.0.0.1:8000

## What is included

- Multi-user configuration loading from config/config.yaml
- Configurable source toggles and per-user source selection
- Source registry with pluggable connectors
- Real fetchers for arXiv, Semantic Scholar, and BioRxiv/MedRxiv RSS with fallback behavior
- Optional Google Scholar connector (enabled by config + google extra)
- Agent-based orchestration pipeline: Discovery Agent, Ranking Agent, Summary Agent
- LangGraph state-machine execution for the agent pipeline
- Node chain: Discovery -> Ranking -> Download&Parse -> Summary -> KB Update
- Optional LLM-powered summary (Ollama/OpenAI-compatible) with safe fallback
- Optional Cross-Encoder reranking with graceful fallback when dependency is unavailable
- Configurable persistence backend (SQLite by default, optional ClickHouse)
- Optional Chroma vector upsert for generated summaries
- Parser backend switch (pypdf/marker/docling) with automatic fallback
- Section-aware fallback summarization from parsed markdown headings
- FastAPI dashboard with manual trigger endpoint
- Web source toggles and run history panel
- Scheduler respects per-user frequency (hourly/daily/weekly)
- In-memory circuit breaker for per-source fault isolation and automatic cooldown

## What is intentionally deferred

- Marker/Docling environment bootstrapping scripts and GPU acceleration tuning
- Deep section-level citation grounding and table/figure extraction in summaries
